<TITLE> Nine lawyers to help attorney general in appeal hearing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 5 (bdnews24.com)  The government has appointed nine lawyers to assist the attorney general during appeals hearing of five convicts to reverse their death sentences on charge of killing independence architect 'Bangabandhu' Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. Deputy solicitor Meer Shafiqul Islam signed the appointment letter on Sunday. The appointees are : advocate Anisul Haque, Abdul Matin Khasru, Nurul Islam Sujan MP, Sheikh Fajle Noor Tapash MP, Mosharraf Hossain Kajal, Toufika Karim, Mamtaj Uddin Ahmed Mehdi, Enamul Karim Imam and Imtiaz Uddin Asif. The Appellate Division ended the first day hearing of the Bangabandhu murder trial appeals on Monday. bdn
